                  <handDesc>
                  <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                  <seg type="rubrication">
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኢግዚአብሔር፡</foreign>
                  </seg>
                  <desc>The word for God is systematically rubricated in this book</desc>
                  <desc><locus target="#139r" facs="139">Fol. 139r</locus>: <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur#Ps148">Psalms of
                                                  David, Psalmus 148</title>, <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur#Ps150">Psalms of
                                                  David, Psalmus 150</title> and the tenth biblical canticle employ columetric rubrication</desc>
                  </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#4v" facs="005">Fol. 4v</locus><desc>Drawing of the Great Judgment (?): A bearded man sits center on a throne.  A smiling crowd stand to the right.  Left, an <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1082Angel">Angel</ref> with drawn <term key="sword" ana="#sword"/> herds a crowd of people</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#168v" facs="169">Fol. 168v</locus><desc>Drawing of <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref> <name ref="PRS4306GabraMa"/></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3"><locus target="#169r" facs="169">Fol. 169r</locus><desc>Drawing of what appears to be <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref> <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7049Michael">Michael</persName> with drawn <term key="sword" ana="#sword"/> and wings.  But a caption in pencil says <q>“It is the Savior of the World.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d4">
                      <locus target="#5r #12v #21r #40v #49r #56r #66r #79r #93v #108r #121v #132v #152r #160r" facs="005 013 021 041 056 066 079 094 108 122 133 152 160">Fols. 5r, 12v, 21r, 40v, 49r, 56r, 66r, 79r, 93v, 108r, 121v, 132v, 152r, 160r</locus>
                      <desc>Harags</desc>
                    </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <locus target="#5r" facs="005">Fol. 5r</locus>
                    <desc>opening prayer is a five-line rhyming stanza from the Psalter of the version</desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <desc>Strophe audit markings: throughout the book, marginal notes mark every ten lines</desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <locus target="#18r #53r #73r #130r #167r 134r 136v" facs="018 053 073 130 167 134 137">Fols. 18r, 53r, 73r, 130r, 167r,, </locus>
                    <desc>Examples of scribal intervention:
                      Insertions with symbols and placement of text in upper margin, some written in red ink and some in black ink.
                      134r, 136v has a correction in purple ink
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <locus target="#73r" facs="073">Fol. 73r</locus>
                    <desc>Marks the midpoint with: 1) alternating text in red and black letters on two lines; and 2) a small text in the right margin, <q><foreign xml:lang="gez">ዝየ፡ መንፈቁ፡</foreign> (“here is its half)</q>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a3">
                    <locus target="#77r #82r #83r #98v #112v #122r #140v #141r #144v #157r" facs="077 082 083 099 113 122 141 141 145 157">Fols. 77r, 82r, 83r, 98v, 112v, 122r, 140v, 141r, 144v, 157r</locus>
                    <desc>marginal explanations of the meaning of a verse, some in Amharic and some in Ge’ez, some written in purple ink, and some written in red ink</desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a4">
                    <locus target="#125v #126r" facs="126"> f. 125v-126r, lower margin</locus>
                    <desc>An example of writing text in mirror imaging/void</desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a6">
                    <locus target="#144v" facs="145">Fol. 144v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    Canticle four is: Prayer of Hana, Mother of Samuel, prophet
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a7">
                    <locus target="#153r #154r 156v 159r" facs="153 154 157 159">Fols. 153r, 154r,, </locus>
                    <desc>
                    Explanation of the meaning of the various songs in the Song of Songs: 153r: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ካልእ፡ መኃልይ፡ ዘይዜኑ፡ ርደቶ፡ ለዋህድ፡ ወተሰግዎቶ፡ እምድንግል፡</foreign>, “The second canticle tells the descent of the Word and his incarnation from the Virgin.” 154r: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሣልስ፡ መኃልይ፡ ዘይዜኑ፡ ትስብእተ፡ መለኮት፡ እምድኅረ፡ ፩ ከዊን፡</foreign>, the third canticle tells of the humanity of the divinity after he became one nature.” 156v: <foreign xml:lang="gez">መኃልይ፡ ዘይነግር፡ ውዳሴ፡ መርዓት፡ለመርዓዊሃ፡</foreign>, “This canticle tells of the praise of the bride to her groom.” 159r: <foreign xml:lang="gez">እምዚአሃ፡ ዘዚአሃ፡ ለቤተ ክርስቲያን፡</foreign>, “From her, for her, for the Christian Church.”
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </additions>
                <bindingDesc>
                  <binding xml:id="binding" contemporary="true">
                    <decoNote xml:id="b1">Parchment, four Coptic chain stitches attached with bridle attachments to rough-hewn boards of the traditional wood, covered with tooled leather with fabric and cardboard visible between the turn-ins.</decoNote>
                    <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                      <material key="parchment"/>
                      <material key="wood"/>
                      <material key="leather"/>
                      <material key="textile"/>
                      <material key="cardboard"/>
                    </decoNote>
                  </binding>
                </bindingDesc>
