                  <provenance>The items were collected by James and Marion Rohrbaugh during their missionary work in Ethiopia in the mid-1930s.
                    These were passed to their son, Richard Rohrbaugh, who, in turn, has passed the items onto his son, Douglas Rohrbaugh.
                    The collection was donated to UCLA in 2013</provenance>
